.TH UPDATE 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
update \- update and upgrade the operating system's packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B update
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B update
is a thin convenience wrapper that runs, in order:
.RS
.nf
sudo apt update
sudo apt \-y full\-upgrade
sudo apt \-y autoremove
.fi
.RE
.PP
This updates the OS\-level package set (kernel, system libraries, etc.),
not DigiHub's own scripts. To check for and apply updates to DigiHub
itself, use
.BR dhupdate (1)
instead.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Update and upgrade all system packages:
.B update
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
Reflects the exit status of the last apt command run. There is no error
handling between steps; if
.B "apt update"
fails, the following upgrade/autoremove steps still run against
whatever package index is currently available.
.SH AUTHOR
Steve de Bode \- W0FFS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR dhupdate (1),
.BR apt (8)
